      "date": "2013-04-05 20:47:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: Looks good to me, approved\n\nResubmitted to make a few changes while I was editing the patch anyway:\n- changed the new function names to be of the form {object}_{action}, so that all of the fld_range_*() functions will sort together\n- change LU_SEQ_RANGE_ALL to LU_SEQ_RANGE_ANY and use 0x3 for the value instead of 0x2.  That allows 0x2 to be used as a different value, possibly LU_SEQ_RANGE_MDT_NEW so that it has an actual value instead of 0x0, or some other target type\n- update the commit comment to list the new function names\n- improve some CERROR() message formatting\n- fix up some whitespace issues",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
