        "subject": "LU-2681 fld: shrink seq_type in lsr_flags",
        "message": "LU-2681 fld: shrink seq_type in lsr_flags\n\nIn lu_seq_range, lsr_flags is treated to only hold\nLU_SEQ_RANAGE_MDT, LU_SEQ_RANGE_OST or LU_SEQ_RANGE_ALL.\nBecause they can only be 0, 1, 2, using lsr_flags(32 bits)\nis clearly unnecessary.\n\nThis patch will shrink the current seq_type to 2 bits, so\nother flags can be used in lsr_flags in future.\n\nSigned-off-by: wang di <di.wang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If1ed9e2e8edd7c55f7ef7ed46afbedc455a4b0c0\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
